simulator.payloads
Class Payload

java.lang.Object
  simulator.payloads.Payload
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable<Payload>
Direct Known Subclasses:
CanMailbox, PhysicalPayload
public abstract class Payload
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Payload>, java.lang.Cloneable

A message sent between components in the elevator. Different objects keep a local Payload object that is registered with the Physical or CAN network as a sender or receiver. The values in the payload class are copied from sender objects to receiver objects by the scheduler at the appropriate time. It is important that objects that represent the same state value or message have the same type. This is how the scheduler knows which objects to copy.
